                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/848.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Department of State has the honor to acknowledge the receipt of the
                    memorandum from the Mexican Embassy dated the 23d ultimo, relative to the
                    alleged activities of one Simon Berthold, who is said to be recruiting men in
                    California with Mexican and Ensenada, in Lower California, for their
                    destination.</p>
                <p>The Department of State has had pleasure in transmitting a copy of this
                    memorandum to the Attorney General of the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
